snippet.title: What is Evangelical Exactly?
snippet.description:
Evangelical is a word that has gotten a lot of press lately. The tough part is, Evangelical can mean a lot of different things depending on who you're talking to. So let's walk through the three major eras of Evangelicalism from 19th Century Europe to early 20th Century America to today, and why churches like Commons need to figure out what church looks like after Evangelicalism​.

2:00 - The 19th century European movement away from state churches.
3:35 - The early 20th century American response to fundamentalism.
7:00 - The late 20th century politicization of Christianity.

snippet.title: What is an "Evangelical?"
snippet.description: We hear a lot about Evangelical Christians.  But what IS an Evangelical?  A conservative Christian?  A white Christian?  A white conservative Christian?  It's time to dive into history to discover the fascinating story of Evangelicalism in America - a tale that includes controversies, arguments about the Bible, seminaries and TV shows... oh... and MONKEYS!

snippet.title: Overview of the Entire Bible in 17 Minutes!
snippet.description:
The Bible is comprised of 66 different books written by about 40 authors over a period of about 1,500 years. It has nearly 1,200 chapters and over 30,000 verses. If you were to read a chapter each day, it would take over 3 years to read the entire Bible!

In our newest video release, Christianity Engaged founder, David Erhart, provides an overview of the entire Bible in 17 minutes to help you better understand its story from beginning to end. The video includes a summary of both the Old and New Testaments as well as a short gospel message (the “good news” of Jesus Christ). You may also want to watch our previous video, The Secret Combination to Unlock Understanding the Bible, where we provide an easy-to-memorize numerical combination to help you navigate through the Bible and understand its structure. We hope these two videos are a blessing to you, increase your understanding of the Bible, and encourage you to read the Word of God for yourself. Please share them with your family and friends. God bless!

snippet.title: The 66 Books of the Bible: a Quick Overview
snippet.description:
The Bible is a huge collection of 66 smaller documents, called "books." This video gives you a quick look at what each of these books is about, and shows how all the books fit together into the Protestant Bible we know today.

You can get a summary of each book of the Bible here: https://overviewbible.com/books-of-the-bible/
